reviews.reviewText: I have anew GE stove with those annoying tempi-sensors......Dumbest technology I have seen unless you are an idiot and forget to turn off your stove a lot. reviews.reviewText: These worked fine at first. Then the two large ones started getting hot spots. Now sometimes even at medium high they glow bright red & you can't lower it, you have to shut the burner off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Hot, but not quite the right size
reviews.reviewText: These are replacements for our GE range. The problem is that the size was just not quite right. At first they were slightly off level, over time they got worse and we ordered a more expensive OEM from GE.We just couldn’t cook at an angle anymore, or keep trying to make them fit.The burners are hot, consistent and not a problem.The burners did start to lose their coating and rust slightly within just a few months use.We cook a lot, we needed something that fit better.
